      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly mapped to the clinical hemolysis threshold without surrogate substitution.",
      "rationale": "The model predicts the power-law hemolysis index (HI), which is then converted to NIH via a volume-flow scaling. This indirect mapping introduces additional model-form uncertainty not fully quantified. Achieved gradation 3; required gradation 5."
