    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps identified at MRL 5, the assessment team accepted the package on the basis that Monte Carlo UQ bounds hemolysis predictions conservatively below the clinical threshold across all sampled operating points, and that the identified gaps are documented as epistemic uncertainties subject to future resolution. The ContextOfUse prose description references the 5-point operating range and clinical threshold, providing sufficient narrative context for the decision. No structured applicability constraint or operating envelope object was formally registered, which constitutes the W-ON-02 weakness embedded in this adversarial sample.",
